<paragraph blockId="2.[264,1323,1593,1899]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<bibRefCitation author="Metz" box="[264,538,1593,1619]" pageId="2" pageNumber="16" refString="Metz, M. A., Webb, D. W. &amp; Irwin, M. E. (2003) A review of the genus Psilocephala Zetterstedt (Diptera: Therevidae) with the description of four new genera. Studia Dipterologica, 10 (1), 227 - 266." type="journal article" year="2003">
Metz (Metz 
<emphasis box="[410,469,1593,1618]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[476,538,1593,1619]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="2003.0">2003</number>
</bibRefCitation>
: 
<number box="[542,588,1593,1619]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="239.0">239</number>
) provided an extensive diagnosis for 
<taxonomicName box="[1031,1168,1593,1618]" class="Insecta" family="Therevidae" genus="Nigranitida" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1031,1168,1593,1618]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Nigranitida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The following additions to the diagnosis are based on the species circumscription defined in this revision: body length males 
<quantity box="[554,697,1673,1699]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" metricValueMax="6.7" metricValueMin="5.3" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" unit="mm" value="6.0" valueMax="6.7" valueMin="5.3">5.3–6.7 mm</quantity>
(n= 
<number box="[748,763,1673,1699]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="9.0">9</number>
), females 
<quantity box="[885,1027,1673,1699]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.25" metricValueMax="8.8" metricValueMin="5.7" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" unit="mm" value="7.25" valueMax="8.8" valueMin="5.7">5.7–8.8 mm</quantity>
(n= 
<number box="[1079,1109,1673,1699]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="14.0">14</number>
); male ommatidia smaller ventrally and laterally; male frons lacking setae; ventral lobe with ventral spines; distiphallus lacking apicolateral spines; ejaculatory apodeme bulbous posteriorly, in crosssection flattened dorsoventrally; furca (
<figureCitation box="[736,824,1793,1819]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="5.[264,383,1524,1548]" captionTargetBox="[324,1256,293,1492]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[309,1265,281,1510]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Nigranitida costata 1. Tergite 8, epandrium, cerci, hypoproct, dorsal view (MEI 048204). 2. Sternite 8, hypandrium, gonocoxite, ventral view. 3. Gonocoxite, hypandrium, dorsal view. 4. Gonocoxite, left lateral view. 5. Gonostylus, left lateral view. 6. Aedeagus, dorsal view (inset: ejaculatory apodeme cross­section). 7. Aedeagus, ventral view. 8. Aedeagus, left lateral view. 9. Female head. 10. Female internal reproductive organs (MEI 106765). Scale = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: C = cercus, CD = common duct, DA = dorsal apodeme, Dp = distiphallus, EA = ejaculatory apodeme, Ep a = epandrium, F = furca, GA = gonocoxal apodeme, Gs = gonostylus, Gx = gonocoxite, GxB = gonocoxal bridge, H = hypandrium, Hp = hypoproct, Sp = spermatheca, SpD = spermathecal duct, SpS = spermathecal sac, SS = sensory seta, S 8 = sternite 8, T 8 = tergite 8, VA = ventral apodeme, VL = ventral lobe. Figure 9 modified from Metz et al, 2003." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/158752/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
Fig. 
<number box="[794,824,1793,1819]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
) oval, posterior margin rounded, anterior margin truncate; anterolateral projections short, posteromedial and anteromedial projections absent; spermathecal ducts directed anteriorly.
</paragraph>
